HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1282
By Bulso
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Ava Sandberg on
being named the 2025 WILLCO Awards Girls'
Lacrosse Player of the Year.
WHEREAS, we are pleased to recognize and commend those successful high school
athletes who, through their magnificent exploits, bring honor to Tennessee and serve as
exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable individual is Ava Sandberg of Brentwood High School,
an athlete of extraordinary talent, skill, and dedication, who has proven herself a formidable
competitor in lacrosse; and
WHEREAS, in recognition of her success on the field throughout the school year, Ms.
Sandberg has been named Girls' Lacrosse Player of the Year at the 2025 WILLCO Awards
celebration; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Sandberg helped lead the Brentwood Bruins lacrosse team to the first
Class AA state championship in the sport's first season sanctioned by the TSSAA; and
WHEREAS, Ava Sandberg epitomizes all that is good in today's student athlete, as she
has achieved a high level of success in sports while evincing great character; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Sandberg's notable achievements are a source of great pride for her
family, her community, and her school, and it is appropriate that we recognize this accomplished
athlete; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Ava Sandberg on being named the 2025
WILLCO Awards Girls' Lacrosse Player of the Year, wishing her much success and happiness
in her future endeavors.
